Lint**: `next lint` CLI command was removed in Next.js 16. Use `eslint .` directly with flat config. `eslint-config-next@16` exports a flat config array natively — no need for `@eslint/eslintrc` FlatCompat wrapper.\n- **Tailwind CSS v4**: Uses `@import \"tailwindcss\"` and `@theme {}` blocks in CSS instead of `tailwind.config.js`. Custom colors defined via `--color-*` CSS variables in `@theme`.\n- **Custom colors**: Access via `text-text-primary`, `bg-background`, `bg-accent`, etc. (Tailwind v4 maps `--color-*` to utility classes automatically).\n- **Font**: Inter loaded via `next/font/google` with `variable: \"--font-inter\"`, applied to `<html>` class. CSS uses `--font-sans` in `@theme` block.\n- **Package manager**: pnpm installed at `$HOME/.local/bin/pnpm` (nix store is read-only). Always `export PATH=\"$HOME/.local/bin:$PATH\"` before pnpm commands.\n\n---\n\n## 2026-02-17 - web-video-l39.1\n- Initialized Next.js 16 project with TypeScript, App Router, Tailwind CSS v4, ESLint 9\n- Configured dark theme with custom color palette (background #0a0a0a, surface #141414, accent purple #6d28d9)\n- Set up Inter font via next/font/google\n- Created base layout (app/layout.tsx) with dark background, text colors, and antialiased rendering\n- Created placeholder home page (app/page.tsx) with hero-like content\n- Created folder structure: app/, components/, lib/\n- **Files changed:**\n  - `package.json` - scripts, dependencies\n  - `tsconfig.json` - TypeScript config (auto-updated by Next.js)\n  - `next.config.ts` - Next.js config\n  - `postcss.config.mjs` - PostCSS with @tailwindcss/postcss\n  - `eslint.config.mjs` - ESLint flat config with eslint-config-next\n  - `app/globals.css` - Tailwind v4 theme with custom dark colors\n  - `app/layout.tsx` - Root layout with Inter font and dark theme\n  - `app/page.tsx` - Home page placeholder\n  - `.gitignore` - Standard Next.js gitignore\n- **Learnings:**\n  - Next.js 16 removed the `next lint` CLI command; use `eslint .` directly\n  - `eslint-config-next@16` exports flat config natively, no FlatCompat needed\n  - Tailwind CSS v4 uses `@theme {}` blocks instead of `tailwind.config.js`\n  - pnpm can't be installed globally in nix — use `--prefix=$HOME/.local`\n  - `create-next-app` refuses to run in non-empty directories; manual setup is more reliable\n---\n\n## 2026-02-17 - web-video-l39.2\n- Created Hero section component (`components/Hero.tsx`) with title, accent-colored keyword, subtitle, and CTA button\n- Updated `app/page.tsx` to import and render the Hero component with a `#compresor` anchor placeholder\n- Hero is fully responsive (text scales from `text-4xl` on mobile to `text-6xl` on desktop)\n- CTA button uses `<a href=\"#compresor\">` to scroll to the future compressor section\n- **Files changed:**\n  - `components/Hero.tsx` - New Hero section component\n  - `app/page.tsx` - Updated to use Hero component\n- **Learnings:**\n  - The `@/` path alias works out of the box with Next.js 16 + TypeScript for importing from project root\n  - Using `text-accent-light` for keyword emphasis works well with the existing theme palette\n---\n\n## 2026-02-17 - web-video-l39.4\n- Created `VideoUpload` component (`components/VideoUpload.tsx`) with drag & drop and click-to-select functionality\n- Component validates file types against both MIME types and file extensions for robustness\n- Displays file name, size (formatted), and format after selection\n- Error message shown when non-video file is selected\n- Created `CompressorSection` wrapper component (`components/CompressorSection.tsx`) as client component to manage upload state\n- Updated `app/page.tsx` to replace placeholder anchor with `CompressorSection`\n- **Files changed:**\n  - `components/VideoUpload.tsx` - New video upload component with drag & drop\n  - `components/CompressorSection.tsx` - New client wrapper for the compressor section\n  - `app/page.tsx` - Replaced placeholder anchor with CompressorSection\n- **Learnings:**\n  - Client components (`\"use client\"`) are needed for drag & drop and file input state management in Next.js App Router\n  - Wrapping interactive sections in a dedicated client component (CompressorSection) keeps the page.tsx as a server component\n  - The `SelectedFile` interface is exported for reuse by future components (US-005 compression input)\n  - Tailwind v4 custom colors work with opacity modifiers (e.g., `bg-accent/10`, `bg-accent/15`) out of the box\n  - Dual validation (MIME type + extension) handles edge cases where browsers report different MIME types for the same format\n---\n\n## 2026-02-17 - web-video-l39.5\n- Added target size input (MB) with validation to `CompressorSection`\n- Validations: minimum 1 MB, must be less than original file size, numeric input\n- Created API route `app/api/compress/route.ts` using `fluent-ffmpeg` for server-side compression\n- API route calculates video bitrate from target size and video duration (reserves 128kbps for audio)\n- Compression uses single-pass encoding with `-movflags +faststart` for web-optimized output\n- Added spinner animation on compress button during compression\n- Added animated progress bar indicator during compression\n- Error state with retry button and descriptive error messages\n- Success state shows compressed size vs original, download button, and \"compress another\" reset\n- Download generates descriptive filename (e.g., `video_compressed_9.00mb.mp4`)\n- Configured `next.config.ts` with `serverExternalPackages: [\"fluent-ffmpeg\"]` for proper server-side usage\n- Installed `fluent-ffmpeg` + `@types/fluent-ffmpeg` dependencies\n- **Files changed:**\n  - `components/CompressorSection.tsx` - Added target size input, compress button, progress, error/success states\n  - `app/api/compress/route.ts` - New API route for server-side FFmpeg compression\n  - `next.config.ts` - Added `serverExternalPackages` for fluent-ffmpeg\n  - `package.json` - Added fluent-ffmpeg dependency and @types/fluent-ffmpeg dev dependency\n- **Learnings:**\n  - `fluent-ffmpeg` is deprecated but still functional; it's the most common Node.js FFmpeg wrapper\n  - Next.js App Router API routes use `formData()` on the request to handle file uploads natively (no body-parser config needed)\n  - `serverExternalPackages` in next.config.ts is needed to prevent Next.js from bundling native/CLI-dependent packages like fluent-ffmpeg\n  - Bitrate calculation: `videoBitrate = (targetSizeBytes * 8 - audioBitrate * duration) / duration` — must subtract audio bits from total budget\n  - Streaming response with `ReadableStream` from `createReadStream` works well for returning large files from API routes\n  - Custom headers like `X-Compressed-Size` can be read client-side from `response.headers.get()` for metadata about the result\n---\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":96,"oldLines":3,"newStart":96,"newLines":19,"lines":["   - Streaming response with `ReadableStream` from `createReadStream` works well for returning large files from API routes","   - Custom headers like `X-Compressed-Size` can be read client-side from `response.headers.get()` for metadata about the result"," ---","+","+## 2026-02-17 - web-video-l39.3","+- Created `Features` component (`components/Features.tsx`) with 4 feature cards in a responsive grid","+- Features: sin límite de tamaño, todos los formatos, tamaño exacto, 100% gratis","+- Each card has an inline SVG icon (Heroicons), title, and description","+- Cards use dark theme: `bg-surface`, `border-border`, hover to `bg-surface-hover`/`border-border-hover`","+- Icon container uses `bg-accent/10` with `text-accent-light` for purple accent","+- Responsive grid: 1 col mobile, 2 col `sm`, 4 col `lg`","+- Updated `app/page.tsx` to render Features between Hero and CompressorSection","+- **Files changed:**","+  - `components/Features.tsx` - New features/benefits section component","+  - `app/page.tsx` - Added Features import and rendering","+- **Learnings:**","+  - Inline SVGs from Heroicons work cl